      <listEvent>
        <event type="researchStep">
          <head type="stepTitle" xml:lang="en"> Visualisation </head>
          <desc type="definition" xml:lang="en">
            <p>Decide what the final user will be able to see of our work: i.e. formats,
              interactivity, access to metadata and sources, etc. Final outputs can include: <list>
                <item>images (that could be printed as well, which for a cultural heritage site is
                  still important),</item>
                <item>videos (depending on a budget), </item>
                <item>interactive viewers (and which one),</item>
                <item>virtual reality (what type of device will be supported)</item>
                <item>if sources will be made available and in what formats</item>
                <item>website to host all the material</item>
              </list>
            </p>
            <p>Level of accuracy and details can be varied depending on: <list>
                <item>explicit annotations linking to sources</item>
                <item>resolution</item>
                <item>accessibility to documentation of the reconstruction process (technical
                  metadata)</item>
                <item>context of the reconstruction (and possibility of updates)</item>
              </list></p>
          </desc>
